The paper presents a generative model for representing and reasoning about events in continuous time, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The model is applied to the domain of networked and distributed computing environments, which falls under the category of systems and networking (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of hypothesis testing for dependence discovery and change-point detection, which involves statistical analysis and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper formalizes the relationship between the proposed model and the noisy-or gate, which is a concept in probabilistic graphical models and machine learning (cs.NE).
